reviews.name: Labette Health

reviews_data.review_text: Daughter called sat thinking her water broke. They told her it was probably sweat since it was hot. They told my daughter to put a pad on and see if she leaked anymore, which she did not. I expressed concern but my daughter thought she had spoke to experts and that she was overreacting. She had a appointment with her specialist today only to find out her water had broke. Do not trust this hospital and they better pray my daughter and grand-baby are okay after they did not provide adequate health care. Daughter is currently on her way to a real hospital!

I could not have asked for better care. My nurse, mu nurse anesthetist; my aides; my surgeon…great team! Even the clerk who checked me in was pleasant! Thank you for continued good care over the decades! Don’t change a thing! Thank you!

To be honest I don't know much of anything about Labette Health other than I was born there on Wednesday January 20th, 1971 at 10:12AM. I lived at 1700 Morgan. My family moved to Wichita, Kansas in 1976. So I don't know anything about this Hospital other than it brought me into this world. Thank you. May God bless you always!
My sister works there and my husband had hip surgery there. He had excellent care and is doing well 9 no after surgery.
They literally tried to send my mom home with a leaking appendix, the nurses are rude, and they don't give updates or important info. This place is the worst hospital I've ever been to.

You ppl who have large issues with a small community comprehensive hospital of many speciality departments more than likely have never seen the other side of any large mega hospital. My knee surgery 10/2021 was personalized and initiated by Dr Meister on day one at the end of his long day out of town at a satellite facility Dr Meister came in and did an evaluation at 5:30 pm, or so & scheduled a surgery for the NEXT day. I had a minimal stay & nothing more than was necessary. Dr's follow up instructions were explained point by point. My preconceived notions of professional medical staff were proven so wrong. But then I behaved as an adult. Not the werewolf children who leave negative comments on this facility. Thanks Dr Meister and all others in your staff Joe . . .

In radiology not sure who guy was but tall guy working for hospital tell family I thought appt wouldn't show up and also commented about financial paper for us not professional at all my husband has dealt with back issues for 10 yrs and due to people like him everyone said he was faking so not cool at all what that radiology guy did at all

Phenomenal doctors and nursing staff.  We’ve been using Labette Health services since I can remember (LCMC!) and have always been treated with compassion and respect. Wouldn’t dream of taking my loved ones anywhere else for top-tier care.

Emergency room staff genuinely care.  Dr. Bryan took the time to explain and allow me to ask questions.
The nurse was caring and explained what she was going to do and why.  Great community hospital.

Used to be a place you could count on for a good Hospital, but those days are gone! Doctors here are some of the worst! Doctor Legler is just out to take patients money, but could care less about their health or well being. Doctor Bryan only pretends to care for you on an emergency room visits that costs you thousands, won't help you unless you come in to the emergency room and then nothing. He will have a young nurse take your blood pressure, weigh your weight on the weight scale and that's about it. My Father is 63 years old and him and I have given this Hospital and Doctors many chances to do better and nothing changes! Wouldn't take a family member here again or a stranger. This Hospital should be closed if that's the best Doctors they can hire or find!

Their nursing staff is very unprofessional. I was waiting for my surgery with no food or drink since 12 the night before... Because that's what you have to do before surgery... It took them four hours to get me into surgery and during that time the nursing staff was eating food in front of seven people who are dehydrated and hungry. My surgeon did a good job, but the only one of the nursing staff who seemed to actually care about any of the patients was Doug. Thank you Doug. Other than that it was awful.

Staff was very pleasant and caring.  Housekeeping and CNA’s needs major improvement.  My husband was in LH for 5 days. Housekeeping came in one time during his stay. Emptied trash and mopped the floor. Cleaned bathroom.  Family members assisted pt with his ADL’s.  And linen change.

Got out of bed and was in severe back pain. Ambulance took me to hospital. When doctor came in he said he could not help me other then give me something for pain. Said I needed to have life threatening problems or they could not help me. No x-rays, no mris, or cat scans. I had to walk out of hospital as they never came back to release me. I will have to move away from Parsons in order to be near a working hospital!. This hospital needs to be shut down.

I went in because my neurologist told me to go in. This is my first trip to any ER in Kansas. I sat there for 3 hours in pain. I understand the people in the lobby that were there before me got pulled back before me. But when people that came after me were taken back I started asking questions. The ladies up front were great although they didn’t have a lot of information as to why I was still sitting there. I really hope this is the status quo for EMERGENCY care.

Its one thing to have construction but NOT in a hospital than patients need rest.  It BS to have some working till 5Am
I needed rest for procedures today and had to listen to that noise all night.  Take care of your patients and not construction at 1.2.3.4.5AM.
Its ridiculous.

Very friendly and helpful staff there. Then the doctors an nurses were very helpful and informative. They didn’t just come in take vitals, scribble in my patient file, ask what’s the problem, then just write a prescription without checking side effects with other medications I am taking.
reviews_data.owner_answer: First and foremost, we hope you're doing well!  Secondly, thanks so much for the 5-Star review and for choosing Labette Health for your healthcare needs.

reviews_data.review_text: My husband is going through dialysis..but I work at labette health..I want to thank scheduleing and registration and others for their kindness. It brings me to tears to know that we are  not going thru this all alone. Thank you all and God Bless you all 💗

Dr Meister is super caring and is brutally honest with his patients. You may not want to hear what he has to say but he won't lie to you. I recommend him every time!! Super caring hospital and a big thank you to most of those working here!!!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for choosing Labette Health and we hope you're recovering well!

reviews_data.review_text: Two strong Females escorted me to the ER.  I entered because of scary Cardiac Systems that had gotten worse.  First thing, a Nurse directed a "Nursing Student" to install an IV.  She stuck my left arm in three places, then went to my right arm with sticks and wound up under my right wrist, which is a painful area for a large IV Needle.  TO A SENIOR CITIZEN (75) WHO IS PRESENTING WITH SERIOUS CARDIAC SYMPTOMS???????
reviews_data.owner_answer: Please contact us directly as we have no record of you receiving recent care in our ER's.  You can contact us via our website or email us at kerrib@labettehealth.com

reviews_data.review_text: I went to the ER with an infection in my leg (upper thigh area) that was causing me lots of pain. It was deep and hasn't fully came to surface. Dr. Glover was there and wouldn't look at it. He wanted to give me an antibiotic and send me home. He said "I'm sure it will be fine". I got mad and walked out. I then went to Neodesha hospital. The ER Dr. Raymond looked at it. He then drained, packed it, gave antibiotic. He actually cared which the Parsons er dr did not.
